# Option A — Xcode Run scheme (recommended for development)
# Product → Scheme → Edit Scheme → Run → Arguments → Environment Variables:
# The *Name* column must be exactly SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (not your URL as the name).
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_public_key_here
#
# If the app still says "Needs config", Xcode may be using a *personal* scheme
# (xcuserdata) without env vars. Fix: Scheme → Manage Schemes… → delete the
# non-shared duplicate, or add SUPABASE_* to your personal scheme too.
#
# Fallback without Xcode env: create this file (sandbox container path):
#   ~/Library/Containers/<BUNDLE_ID>/Data/Library/Application Support/Presence/Supabase.plist
# Use the same keys/values as Secrets.example.plist. Create the "Presence" folder if needed.

# Option B — Secrets.plist in the app bundle
# Copy Presence/Presence/Secrets.example.plist → Secrets.plist, fill values,
# keep Secrets.plist out of git (see repo .gitignore). File must live next to
# other sources so the synchronized group includes it in the target.

# Required: Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Anonymous sign-ins → ON

# Tune In: enable MusicKit on the App ID; add com.apple.developer.music-kit to
# Presence.entitlements when using full development signing.
